The paper deals with the problem of planning collision-free paths for multiple agents, which is a common problem in robotics and control systems. The use of optimization methods known as proximal algorithms is the main focus of the paper. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with incorporating different proximal operators, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with decentralization and optimality criteria, which are common topics in control systems and systems engineering, making cs.SY a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with multi-agent systems, which is a common topic in multi-agent systems and game theory, making cs.MA a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with numerical experiments and performance evaluation, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG a likely sub-category.
